🔧 How to Run

Open Arduino IDE.

Install ESP8266 board package (Boards Manager → search “ESP8266” → install).

Select NodeMCU 1.0 (ESP-12E Module) under Tools → Board.

Replace YOUR_WIFI_SSID and YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD.

Wire relays:

IN1 → D1

IN2 → D2

IN3 → D3

IN4 → D4

VCC → 5V, GND → GND

Upload the code.

Open Serial Monitor → Copy IP Address.

Open browser → type http://<IP> → control appliances!
